00:20:53.110 --> 00:20:59.980 position:75%
I think I'll begin, though, Sahr, with a general
question for you about the library's collection.

00:20:59.980 --> 00:21:04.200
So how is it that the library
came to hold the Wilson papers

00:21:04.200 --> 00:21:07.860
and then how do researchers
generally access them?

00:21:07.860 --> 00:21:11.900 position:66%
As the main curator for the Wilson papers,
tell us a little bit about the life

00:21:11.900 --> 00:21:14.480 position:56%
of those papers here at the library.

00:21:14.480 --> 00:21:23.820 position:70%
&gt;&gt; So actually shorter after Woodrow Wilson
left office, the Library of Congress embarked

00:21:23.820 --> 00:21:29.180 position:64%
on a major effort to collect presidential
papers, including Woodrow Wilson's.

00:21:29.180 --> 00:21:33.890 position:66%
And so in the early 20th century, a number

00:21:33.890 --> 00:21:39.270 position:59%
of presidential paper collections were
brought to the Library of Congress.

00:21:39.270 --> 00:21:47.560 position:69%
Wilson's were donated by his family and some
of them came directly from the White House.

00:21:47.560 --> 00:21:56.560 position:72%
And the Library of Congress has been a major
repository for presidential papers ever since.

00:21:56.560 --> 00:21:59.730 position:70%
We have the papers of 23 American presidents.

00:21:59.730 --> 00:22:07.100 position:73%
The most of the 20th century presidents after
Calvin Coolidge now have presidential libraries

00:22:07.100 --> 00:22:10.890 position:66%
where you can use the presidential papers.

00:22:10.890 --> 00:22:13.960
And those presidential libraries
are run by the national archives.

00:22:13.960 --> 00:22:18.650
But for presidential collections
before Herbert Hoover,

00:22:18.650 --> 00:22:22.840
most of those papers can be
found at the Library of Congress.

00:22:22.840 --> 00:22:26.040 position:56%
Now if you're interested in actually
using the Woodrow Wilson papers,

00:22:26.040 --> 00:22:28.850 position:75%
there are a couple of ways that you can do this.

00:22:28.850 --> 00:22:35.880 position:73%
Most of the Wilson papers have been microfilmed
and so they are available for use on microfilm.

00:22:35.880 --> 00:22:39.830 position:56%
But I know microfilm is not
necessarily the easiest thing to use

00:22:39.830 --> 00:22:43.040 position:61%
so there are a couple of other options.

00:22:43.040 --> 00:22:49.080 position:61%
One is in the not-too-distant future --
in the spring or summer of next year --

00:22:49.080 --> 00:22:52.510
the Woodrow Wilson papers
will be available online.

00:22:52.510 --> 00:22:58.220 position:69%
They're in the process of being digitized
and put on the Library of Congress' website.

00:22:58.220 --> 00:23:01.740
And so they will -- all of the
Wilson papers here at the Library

00:23:01.740 --> 00:23:08.610 position:56%
of Congress will be available on the
website in about six months or so.

00:23:08.610 --> 00:23:11.630 position:59%
Another option for using the papers --

00:23:11.630 --> 00:23:19.420 position:72%
you won't get to see the images of the
original papers this way, but those 69 volumes

00:23:19.420 --> 00:23:23.730
of the papers of Woodrow Wilson
by Arthur Link that I mentioned

00:23:23.730 --> 00:23:29.880 position:70%
in my talk are really the most accessible
way today, tomorrow, for the next six months,

00:23:29.880 --> 00:23:35.090 position:73%
of getting access to many of the most important
papers from the Woodrow Wilson collection.

00:23:35.090 --> 00:23:41.910 position:64%
And even though it's 69 volumes, it's not
anywhere close to the entire collection,

00:23:41.910 --> 00:23:46.200
all 300,000 documents that we
have at the Library of Congress.

00:23:46.200 --> 00:23:51.320 position:61%
But remember that not every document in
the Woodrow Wilson papers was written

00:23:51.320 --> 00:23:58.750 position:70%
by Woodrow Wilson or gives you a deep insight
about him, his life, and his presidency.

00:23:58.750 --> 00:24:00.060 position:59%
Does that answer your question, Naomi?

00:24:00.060 --> 00:24:00.990
